messages.content:
Ashley, and I’m a lover of all things creative.

I am obsessed with learning new skills, finding the best tools to get my work done, and I’m on a mission to find the most effective ways to manage all of my tasks. As you can see, I love a good checklist!

I have a Bachelor’s degree in Communications and Media Arts from the University of Oregon, where I graduated with honors. While there, I was a student worker in the UO Marketing & Communications office and served as an undergraduate teaching assistant for three courses. Through this experience, I developed a passion for design and marketing, specifically in the realm of social media.

I have over six years of experience working with brands to develop creative campaigns and content for their social media platforms. I’ve worked in-house, at an ad agency, and as a consultant for small businesses.

I am currently the Marketing Manager for Portland Community College, working with our online marketing team to create and implement social media strategies.

I am passionate about supporting small businesses, helping creatives find their voice online, and increasing diversity in the digital space.
